Warnings have been thrown, so enjoy the projects. This wiki is using several tools; you may test them in [[standalone versions]]. Do not hesitate to [[contribute|Contributing]]. Another way to push your favourite project forward is becoming a [[patron|Patron?]].

!! <<f-i globe>> [[i18n Macro]] ({{$:/core/macros/i18n!!version}})
the <$link to="$:/core/macros/i18n"><<f-i download>> i18n macro</$link> will help you to have a multilingual wiki if you wish without hacking internal //language + lingo// system in TiddlyWiki... You may also appreciate associated [[translation helper tool|i18n translation helper]].

!! <<f-i map>> [[Leaflet maps plugin]] ({{$:/plugins/sycom/leaflet!!version}})
the <$link to="$:/plugins/sycom/leaflet"><<f-i download>> Leaflet maps plugin</$link> will embed leaflet maps in your tiddlywiki with the `<$leafmap />` widget. See the [[Michel Strogoff|Michel Strogoff from the sky]] (map below) or [[included doc examples|$:/plugins/sycom/leaflet/example]] to learn more.

The plugins also brings the <<f-i map-pin>> [[geoLocationWidget]] which creates a button to collect the current geolocation of your browser. But it may be used independently if you do not need the plugin...

